.help cnvtsec March2005 gemini.gemtools
.ih
NAME
cnvtsec -- Convert a date and time to seconds
.ih
USAGE
cnvtsec dateobs timeobs
.ih
PARAMETERS
.ls dateobs
The date string.  This string can be a fully specified date
and time using the standard FITS format 
(YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.SS).  It can also contain only the
date (YYYY-MM-DD), in which case the time must be given
by \fItimeobs\fR.
.le
.ls timeobs
The time string (HH:MM:SS.SS).  This string must be
non-empty if the time is not included in \fIdateobs\fR.
.le
.ls status = 0
Exit status will be non-zero if the task halted with an error.  This parameter
is always set by the task, and should not be modified by the user.
.le
.ih
DESCRIPTION
This task converts a date and time (FITS format) to a number of seconds
since 00:00:00 01-Jan-80, and prints it.  The fractional parts of
seconds are conserved.  Note that leap-seconds are ignored.  This task
is particularly useful to calculate time intervals between observations.
.ih
EXAMPLES
1. Converted a FITS formated date and time string.
.sp
.nf
    ge> cnvtsec "2005-03-30T15:51:43.45" ""
    796665103.4500
.fi
.sp
2. Converted using a date string and time string.
.sp
.nf
    ge> cnvtsec "2005-03-30" "15:51:43.45"
    796665103.4500
.fi
.ih
